tldr: The user requested a thorough aesthetic review and improvement of their
  sleep questionnaire app. I implemented a new sleep-themed color palette,
  redesigned key UI components, and standardized section styling across the
  entire application to create a more calming and professional user experience.
overview: The user wanted to elevate the aesthetic appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. I began by analyzing the
  existing design, identifying issues like a bland color palette and uninspired
  form elements. My approach involved implementing a new, calming sleep-themed
  color palette, redesigning the main questionnaire form with subtle background
  effects and an improved progress indicator, and enhancing the introductory
  section with engaging feature cards. Key decisions included standardizing the
  look and feel of all interactive form components and introducing a consistent
  "card-style" grouping for all content sections. After an initial round of
  updates, a thorough browser review highlighted that many secondary sections
  still retained the old styling, prompting a comprehensive update across all
  remaining questionnaire sections. The outcome is a significantly more
  polished, professional, and visually harmonious application that better
  reflects its purpose as a sleep health assessment tool.
